document_data.Rumors & Legends:
Legend had it that the derro originally lived on the surface of [[Faer√ªn]].{{Cite digital book/Venom in Her Veins/Kindle|2983}} But they opened ''[[portal]]s'' to the [[Far Realm]], which offended the [[World Serpent]], who cast the derro into the Underdark.{{Cite digital book/Venom in Her Veins/Kindle|3216}}

There were other conflicting legends of how the derro came to be. The [[duergar]] believed that the derro were another dwarf clan that was long held by [[mind flayer]]s, which resulted in the madness that afflicted them. The derro themselves all told oft-changing variations of the myth of their god; all versions shared a common focus on his stealing of [[magic]] from a great evil to help the derro survive through their ideals of deceit and cruelty.

Outside of their origins, there were a few rumors that claimed they ate [[human]] flesh.
